[SN]TITLE[SN]
Mobile phone firm EE to create 60 jobs in Merthyr Tydfil

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Mobile phone operator EE is to create 60 new jobs at its call centre in Merthyr Tydfil.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The firm, which is owned by BT, said the extra roles follow a move to base all customer service calls in the UK and Ireland.
More than 800 people already work at its Rhyd-y-Car Business Park site.
Economy Secretary Ken Skates said it was "excellent news for the local economy".
